This product includes original Apache License 2.0 software and reimplemented
concepts informed by the following QSOL ecosystem repositories. NEXUS integrates
contracts and selected algorithms; it does not redistribute entire repositories.

QSOLKCB/SPECTRAL
https://github.com/QSOLKCB/SPECTRAL
Licence: MIT
Contribution: local browser architecture; deterministic PCM/WAV and store-only
ZIP concepts; canonical artifact, replay, visualization and persistence patterns.
Modifications: generalized into a three-engine runtime, three determinism modes,
shared claim system and NEXUS v1 artifact schemas.

QSOLKCB/QEC
https://github.com/QSOLKCB/QEC
Licence: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
Contribution: recompute-not-trust receipts, canonical proof-artifact concepts,
replay validation and source-bound claim architecture.
Modifications: reimplemented as a lightweight browser provenance layer; no QEC
decoder or QEC runtime is included.

QSOLKCB/QNTOY
https://github.com/QSOLKCB/QNTOY
Licence: MIT
Contribution: three-state audiovisual field-organism concept.
Modifications: uncontrolled randomness and WebAudio-coupled export were replaced
with seeded deterministic evolution, offline PCM, explicit classical boundaries,
measurements, replay artifacts and tests.

QSOLKCB/TFT
https://github.com/QSOLKCB/TFT
Licence: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
DOI: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17587839
Contribution: symmetric tensor transformation/invariance demonstration,
eigenvalue-to-frequency mapping and quadrature stereo concept.
Modifications: reimplemented in dependency-free JavaScript, bounded to 2x2 and
3x3 real symmetric matrices, with numerical residual validation and a claim
boundary that does not infer physical self-duality.

QSOLKCB/UFF
https://github.com/QSOLKCB/UFF
Licence: Apache License 2.0
DOI: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17669627
Reviewed lineage: uff_model.py and DEMO_GALAXY.csv at
e642060626e70f52dcb44daacbffbdbe149a32d0.
Contribution: SPARC-style rotation-curve analysis, comparative model and
sonification concepts, and the replaceable pseudo-isothermal-like UFF profile.
Modifications: reimplemented with canonical units, fail-closed validation,
transparent bounded fitting, versioned model status, and mandatory Experimental
label for uff_experimental_v1.

QSOLKCB/QAI-UFT
https://github.com/QSOLKCB/QAI-UFT
Licence: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
DOI: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17569256
Contribution: ternary, sexagesimal, codon-64, tensor-phase and interface concepts.
Modifications: reimplemented as bounded mathematical and musical mapping helpers;
no React/Vite application or claim of embodied physics is imported.

QSOLKCB/AIMM
https://github.com/QSOLKCB/AIMM
Contribution: future optional narrator/assistant concept only.
No AIMM implementation, remote inference client, system-entropy authority or
trusted numerical role is included in NEXUS 1.0.

